api_list.description:
This response suggests that the server successfully received the JSON payload containing a "prompt" field with the value "Hello, there!". The server then generated a response containing a "bot" field with the value "\n\nHow are you doing today?" in JSON format.

If you want to extract the value of the "bot" field from the response, you can use the Response object's json() method like this:

const response = await fetch("https://............../", {
  method: "POST",
  headers: {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
  },
  body: JSON.stringify({
    prompt: "Hello, there!",
  }),
});
const data = await response.json();
console.log(data.bot); // Output: "\n\nHow are you doing today?"
